75 that one had been predicting the contours of the asian maize economy in 2000 what variables and parameters would forecasters have missed in significant ways this procedure turns out to be a very sobering exercise for anyone now predicting events in 2025 download pdf+ complete modified november 2009 pdf asian_maize_in_2025 pdf 3.6 mb parent research food and nutrition security in an era of economic volatility topics history east asia & the pacific search fse search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages publications of interest hybrid maize a maize simulation model that combines two crop modeling approaches hs yang a dobermann jl lindquist dt walters t arkebauer kenneth cassman field crops research vol 87 2004 html+ cover maize transition in asia unlocking the controversy the rosamond l naylor walter p falcon american journal of agricultural economics vol 80 5 1998 html+ cover support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4920 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
